    <text id="B0427T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Jackson asks Trout to provide transportation for Betsey Brown and her children to
                    Winchester.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands<lb/>Office 4th Division, 9th
                    Sub-District, Virginia.
                    <name type="recipient">N K Trout <abbr expan="Esquire">Esq</abbr><lb/>Mayor
                        &amp;c<lb/>Staunton</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-02-03"><abbr expan="February">Feb</abbr> 3d 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I respectfully refer enclosed papers to you inviting attention to endorsement of
                        <abbr expan="Brigadier General">Brig Genl</abbr> O. Brown <abbr
                        expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst Comr.</abbr> of <abbr
                        expan="January 29, 1868">Jan 29/68</abbr> and requesting that if possible
                    early provision be made to forward Betsey Brown and her three (3) children to
                    Winchester. These papers to be returned.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        <abbr expan="Your obedient servant">Yr obt servt</abbr>
                    </salute>
                    <signed>Thos P. Jackson<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner"
                            >Asst Sub Asst Comr</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
